. Florida wealth migration sustaining HNW custom home demand in Palm Beach + Miami-Dade + Naples + Boca Raton + Coral Gables at $5M-$25M+ price tiers. Florida Statutes Chapter 713 Construction Lien Law governing contractor + subcontractor lien rights with Notice to Owner requirements. Florida Statutes Chapter 440 Workers Compensation requirements. Mortgage qualifying under Fannie Mae B3-3.2-01 self-employed borrower documentation with 2-year personal and business tax returns + Year-to-Date CPA-prepared Profit & Loss statement; Form 1084 cash-flow analysis adding back depreciation (Schedule C line 13, partnership return depreciation, S-corp depreciation) + amortization + business mileage at IRS standard rate ($0.67/mile 2024) + business use of home Form 8829 + Section 179 expensing on equipment and tools with annual limit $1.16M (2024) + entity-level non-cash expenses, typical 15-35% AGI qualifying capacity recovery. Bank Statement Non-QM alternative qualifying on 12-24 months business bank statement deposits with typical 50% expense ratio applied for aggressive-depreciation contractors where Form 1084 still leaves qualifying short. P&L Statement Non-QM qualifying on CPA-prepared profit and loss statement for established practice owners. Asset-Depletion Non-QM converting liquid portfolio balance to implied monthly income amortized over 360 months for HNW retiring contractors. DSCR Debt Service Coverage Ratio Non-QM for investment property portfolio scaling. Construction-to-Permanent single-close financing with owner-builder option for Florida licensed contractors. Multi-source synthesis combining contractor income + spouse W-2 income. Bonding capacity letter supporting continuity narrative. General liability + workers compensation + completed operations + performance and payment bond insurance cash expenses. Florida no state income tax cash flow advantage." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/real-estate-professionals/builder-contractor/">
